From: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 19:51:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7915: fix tx retry and failure counting

The v3 tx_failed formula added retries to the failure flag, treating
every successful retry as a failure.  Guard count-1 against unsigned
underflow when hardware reports zero attempts.

Remove the v0 TX_FREE path -- its COUNT field is a status code, not
an attempt count; MT7915 uses PPDU TXS for these counters instead.

Remove the WED gate -- v3 chips need TX_FREE counting regardless of
WED state.

Signed-off-by: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
---
 mt7915/mac.c |   21 ++++++---------------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

--- a/mt7915/mac.c
+++ b/mt7915/mac.c
@@ -900,22 +900,13 @@ mt7915_mac_tx_free(struct mt7915_dev *de
 			continue;
 		}
 
-		if (!mtk_wed_device_active(&mdev->mmio.wed) && wcid) {
-			u32 tx_retries = 0, tx_failed = 0, count;
+		if (wcid && v3 && (info & MT_TX_FREE_MPDU_HEADER_V3)) {
+			u32 count = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_COUNT_V3, info);
 
-			if (v3 && (info & MT_TX_FREE_MPDU_HEADER_V3)) {
-				count = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_COUNT_V3, info);
-				tx_retries = count ? count - 1 : 0;
-				tx_failed = tx_retries +
-					!!FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_STAT_V3, info);
-			} else if (!v3 && (info & MT_TX_FREE_MPDU_HEADER)) {
-				count = FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_COUNT, info);
-				tx_retries = count ? count - 1 : 0;
-				tx_failed = tx_retries +
-					!!FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_STAT, info);
-			}
-			wcid->stats.tx_retries += tx_retries;
-			wcid->stats.tx_failed += tx_failed;
+			if (count)
+				wcid->stats.tx_retries += count - 1;
+			wcid->stats.tx_failed +=
+				!!FIELD_GET(MT_TX_FREE_STAT_V3, info);
 		}
 
 		if (v3 && (info & MT_TX_FREE_MPDU_HEADER_V3))
